    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Methodology - Geospatial Syllabus Explorer</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
    <style>
        /* Paste the same CSS from index.html here for consistency */
        :root { --primary: #2c3e50; --accent: #3498db; --light: #ecf0f1; }
        body { margin: 0; font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 100vh;}
        nav { background: var(--primary); padding: 1rem 2rem; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; color: white; }
        nav a { color: white; text-decoration: none; margin-left: 20px; }
        .container { max-width: 800px; margin: 3rem auto; padding: 0 2rem; flex-grow: 1; }
        h1 { border-bottom: 3px solid var(--accent); padding-bottom: 10px; color: var(--primary); }
        h3 { color: var(--accent); margin-top: 2rem; }
        footer { background: var(--primary); color: #bdc3c7; text-align: center; padding: 2rem; margin-top: auto; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <nav>
        <div class="logo">Geospatial Syllabus Explorer</div>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="explorer.html">Map</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Methodology</h1>
        <p>The data presented in this explorer is generated through automated text.</p>

        <h3>1. Data Collection</h3>
        <p>Syllabi are collected from publicly available university websites and voluntary submissions. Files are stored in a central repository.</p>

        <h3>2. Text Extraction</h3>
        <p>I use Python-based OCR and PDF parsing libraries to extract raw text from syllabus documents, preserving the structure where possible.</p>

        <h3>3. AI Classification</h3>
        <p>Each syllabus is analyzed to determine:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Course Level:</strong> Inferred from course codes (e.g., 100-200 vs. 500+).</li>
            <li><strong>Assessment Type:</strong> Analysis of grading rubrics (e.g., identifying "Project" weight vs "Exam" weight).</li>
            <li><strong>Tech Stack:</strong> Keyword matching for specific software (ArcGIS, QGIS, Python) and hardware (Drone, GPS).</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4. Verification</h3>
        <p>While automated, the database allows for manual correction. If you spot an error in your course listing, please use the Contact page to request an update.</p>
    </div>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2026 Dr. Jochen Albrecht, GISP. All Rights Reserved.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
